<div class="indented"><a id="comment-8532"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/daybreak-part-one#comment-8532" class="active">Who knows what is good or bad?</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Sat, 2009-03-14 07:47.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Being useful and kind is an effective way of getting someone to do what you want, and making them think they're on top and you like them. They also end up doing most of the work for you which is less costly and distracting than banging heads.</p>
<p>At the opposite end of the scale we have inverse snobbery. This can be explained by closed minds and selfishness. People often fear what they don't understand or loss, so end up trying to impose familiar patterns and ties on someone else.</p>
<p>Who knows what is good or bad?</p>
</div>
